  "body": "Currently getTransactionReceipt returns:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n{\r\n  blockHash: \"0x...\",\r\n  blockNumber: 11111111,\r\n  contractAddress: null,\r\n  cumulativeGasUsed: 1111111,\r\n  from: \"0x...\",\r\n  gasUsed: 1111111,\r\n  logs: [{\r\n      address: \"0x...\",\r\n      blockHash: \"0x...\",\r\n      blockNumber: 11111111,\r\n      data: \"0x...\",\r\n      logIndex: 11,\r\n      removed: false,\r\n      topics: [\"0x...\"],\r\n      transactionHash: \"0x...\",\r\n      transactionIndex: 11\r\n  }],\r\n  logsBloom: \"0x...\",\r\n  status: \"0x1\",\r\n  to: \"0x...\",\r\n  transactionHash: \"0x...\",\r\n  transactionIndex: 11\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI would propose adding a new key to the object called `ethAccountsAffected` with an array of objects, the objects have an address, and an amount with a minus sign before it when subtracted.\r\n\r\nThis way we could look at a transaction and know exactly how certain addresses were affected in their ETH balance by the results of a smart contract.\r\n\r\nI apologize if someone has already proposed this, and if the data key of the logs is in a format that reliably tells this info, I would still like to ask that this data is duplicated in a more easy to handle format such as I explained above.",
